The paper deals with the compression of de Bruijn graphs, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and computational efficiency (cs.CE). The algorithm described in the paper involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are also related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the Burrows-Wheeler transform (BWT) and its compression technique called tunneling, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
